.TH "input_mt_report_pointer_emulation" 9 "input_mt_report_pointer_emulation" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
input_mt_report_pointer_emulation \- common pointer emulation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" input_mt_report_pointer_emulation
.BI "(struct input_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "bool use_count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
input device with allocated MT slots
.IP "use_count" 12
report number of active contacts as finger count
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Performs legacy pointer emulation via BTN_TOUCH, ABS_X, ABS_Y and
ABS_PRESSURE. Touchpad finger count is emulated if use_count is true.

The input core ensures only the KEY and ABS axes already setup for
this device will produce output.
